2. name: creating-rtk-query-endpoints
3. description: Creates RTK Query API endpoints using the ApiConfig[] + ProtectedApiService pattern with built-in MSW mocks. Use when adding new API endpoints, creating API services, mocking endpoints, or connecting the frontend to a backend API.
4. ---
5. 
6. # RTK Query API Endpoints
7. 
8. Uses `ApiConfig[]` + `ProtectedApiService` pattern with built-in MSW mocks. Never use legacy `fetchData()`.
9. 
10. ## Step 1 ΓÇö Add Endpoint Constant
11. 
12. File: `src/libs/http/api-endpoints.ts`
13. 
14. ```typescript
15. export const API_ENDPOINTS = {
16.   // ... existing endpoints
17. 
18.   // Add new endpoint with :id placeholder for dynamic segments
19.   FEATURE_ACTION: '/api/{feature}/{resource}',
20.   FEATURE_ACTION_BY_ID: '/api/{feature}/{resource}/:id/{sub-resource}',
21. } as const;
22. ```
23. 
24. **Naming convention:** `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`, grouped by feature with comments.
25. 
26. ## Step 2 ΓÇö Define TypeScript Types
27. 
28. File: `src/types/{feature}.ts` (create new file or add to existing)
29. 
30. ```typescript
31. /** Request type for creating a resource */
32. export interface CreateResourceRequest {
33.   name: string;
34.   // ... fields
35. }
36. 
37. /** Response type from the API */
38. export interface CreateResourceResponse {
39.   success: boolean;
40.   data: {
41.     id: number;
42.     // ... fields
43.   };
44.   message?: string;
45. }
46. 
47. /** Response for GET queries */
48. export interface ResourceListResponse {
49.   success: boolean;
50.   data: ResourceItem[];
51.   message?: string;
52. }
53. ```
54. 
55. **Rules:**
56. - Types go in `src/types/` ΓÇö never define inline in components
57. - Export interfaces, not type aliases, for API contracts
58. - Include `success`, `data`, `message?` wrapper for all responses
59. 
60. ## Step 3 ΓÇö Add RTK Query Endpoint with MSW Mock
61. 
62. File: `src/libs/store/api/{feature}Api.ts`
63. 
64. ### For a NEW feature API file:
65. 
66. ```typescript
67. import { API_ENDPOINTS, BASE_URL } from '@/libs/http/api-endpoints';
68. import { http, HttpResponse } from 'msw';
69. import type {
70.   CreateResourceRequest,
71.   CreateResourceResponse,
72.   ResourceListResponse,
73. } from '@/types/{feature}';
74. import { QueryBuilder, ApiConfig, ProtectedApiService } from './apiConfig';
75. 
76. export const apiConfigs: ApiConfig[] = [
77.   // --- GET query ---
78.   {
79.     url: `${BASE_URL.DATAHUB}${API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_LIST}`,
80.     endpoint: 'getResources',
81.     builder(builder: QueryBuilder, url: string) {
82.       return builder.query<ResourceListResponse, void>({
83.         query: () => API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_LIST,
84.         providesTags: ['Feature'],
85.       });
86.     },
87.     mock() {
88.       return http.get(this.url, async () => {
89.         await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 800));
90.         return HttpResponse.json({
91.           success: true,
92.           data: [/* realistic mock data */],
93.           message: 'Resources fetched successfully',
94.         });
95.       });
96.     },
97.   },
98. 
99.   // --- GET query with parameter ---
100.   {
101.     url: `${BASE_URL.DATAHUB}${API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_BY_ID}`,
102.     endpoint: 'getResourceById',
103.     builder(builder: QueryBuilder, url: string) {
104.       return builder.query<ResourceResponse, number>({
105.         query: (id) => API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_BY_ID.replace(':id', id.toString()),
106.         providesTags: (_result, _error, id) => [{ type: 'Feature', id }],
107.         refetchOnMountOrArgChange: true,
108.       });
109.     },
110.     mock() {
111.       return http.get(this.url.replace(':id', ':resourceId'), async ({ params }) => {
112.         await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
113.         const resourceId = params.resourceId as string;
114.         return HttpResponse.json({
115.           success: true,
116.           data: { id: Number(resourceId), /* ... */ },
117.         });
118.       });
119.     },
120.   },
121. 
122.   // --- GET query with pagination ---
123.   {
124.     url: `${BASE_URL.DATAHUB}${API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_LIST_PAGINATED}`,
125.     endpoint: 'getResourcesPaginated',
126.     builder(builder: QueryBuilder, url: string) {
127.       return builder.query<PaginatedResponse, { page?: number; limit?: number }>({
128.         query: ({ page = 1, limit = 20 }) => ({
129.           url: API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_LIST_PAGINATED,
130.           params: { page, limit },
131.         }),
132.         providesTags: ['Feature'],
133.       });
134.     },
135.     mock() {
136.       return http.get(this.url, async ({ request }) => {
137.         await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 800));
138.         const url = new URL(request.url);
139.         const page = Number(url.searchParams.get('page') || '1');
140.         const limit = Number(url.searchParams.get('limit') || '20');
141.         // Generate paginated mock data
142.         const allItems = [/* ... */];
143.         const start = (page - 1) * limit;
144.         const items = allItems.slice(start, start + limit);
145.         return HttpResponse.json({
146.           success: true,
147.           data: items,
148.           pagination: { page, limit, total: allItems.length, totalPages: Math.ceil(allItems.length / limit) },
149.         });
150.       });
151.     },
152.   },
153. 
154.   // --- POST mutation ---
155.   {
156.     url: `${BASE_URL.DATAHUB}${API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_CREATE}`,
157.     endpoint: 'createResource',
158.     builder(builder: QueryBuilder, url: string) {
159.       return builder.mutation<CreateResourceResponse, CreateResourceRequest>({
160.         query: (body) => ({
161.           url: API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_CREATE,
162.           method: 'POST',
163.           body,
164.         }),
165.         invalidatesTags: ['Feature'],
166.       });
167.     },
168.     mock() {
169.       return http.post(this.url, async ({ request }) => {
170.         await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1500));
171.         const body = await request.json() as CreateResourceRequest;
172.         return HttpResponse.json({
173.           success: true,
174.           data: { id: Date.now(), ...body },
175.           message: 'Resource created successfully',
176.         });
177.       });
178.     },
179.   },
180. 
181.   // --- POST mutation with FormData (file upload) ---
182.   {
183.     url: `${BASE_URL.DATAHUB}${API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_UPLOAD}`,
184.     endpoint: 'uploadFile',
185.     builder(builder: QueryBuilder, url: string) {
186.       return builder.mutation<UploadResponse, { id: number; file: File }>({
187.         query: ({ id, file }) => {
188.           const formData = new FormData();
189.           formData.append('file', file);
190.           return {
191.             url: API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_UPLOAD.replace(':id', id.toString()),
192.             method: 'POST',
193.             body: formData,
194.           };
195.         },
196.         invalidatesTags: (_result, _error, { id }) => [{ type: 'Feature', id }],
197.       });
198.     },
199.     mock() {
200.       return http.post(this.url.replace(':id', ':resourceId'), async () => {
201.         await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 2000));
202.         return HttpResponse.json({
203.           success: true,
204.           data: { uploaded: true },
205.           message: 'File uploaded successfully',
206.         });
207.       });
208.     },
209.   },
210. 
211.   // --- DELETE mutation ---
212.   {
213.     url: `${BASE_URL.DATAHUB}${API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_DELETE}`,
214.     endpoint: 'deleteResource',
215.     builder(builder: QueryBuilder, url: string) {
216.       return builder.mutation<DeleteResponse, { id: number }>({
217.         query: ({ id }) => ({
218.           url: API_ENDPOINTS.FEATURE_DELETE.replace(':id', id.toString()),
219.           method: 'DELETE',
220.         }),
221.         invalidatesTags: ['Feature'],
222.       });
223.     },
224.     mock() {
225.       return http.delete(this.url.replace(':id', ':resourceId'), async () => {
226.         await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 800));
227.         return HttpResponse.json({ success: true, message: 'Deleted' });
228.       });
229.     },
230.   },
231. ];
232. 
233. // Auto-generates typed hooks: useGetResourcesQuery, useCreateResourceMutation, etc.
234. export const {
235.   useGetResourcesQuery,
236.   useGetResourceByIdQuery,
237.   useGetResourcesPaginatedQuery,
238.   useCreateResourceMutation,
239.   useUploadFileMutation,
240.   useDeleteResourceMutation,
241. } = new ProtectedApiService(apiConfigs).get();
242. ```
243. 
244. ### For an EXISTING feature API file:
245. 
246. Add new `ApiConfig` objects to the existing `apiConfigs` array and export the new hooks.
247. 
248. ## Step 4 ΓÇö Register Tag Type (if new feature)
249. 
250. File: `src/libs/store/api/baseApi.ts`
251. 
252. Add your feature tag to the `tagTypes` array:
253. 
254. ```typescript
255. tagTypes: ['Admin', 'Onboarding', 'Feature'], // Add new tag
256. ```
257. 
258. ## Mock Rules
259. 
260. | Rule | Details |
261. |------|---------|
262. | **Delays** | 800ΓÇô2000ms, added in mock handler, NEVER in components |
263. | **Admin org mocks** | `orgId === '1'` reserved for fresh creation flow, use `localStorage` key `'creatingOrganization'` |
264. | **Realistic data** | Mock data should look real ΓÇö use proper names, dates, amounts |
265. | **Error simulation** | Return `new HttpResponse(null, { status: 404 })` for error cases |
266. | **Auto-registration** | MSW handlers auto-register via `src/libs/http/mocks/browser.ts` ΓÇö no manual registration |
267. 
268. ## Usage in Components
269. 
270. ```typescript
271. // Queries ΓÇö auto-fetch on mount
272. const { data, isLoading, error } = useGetResourcesQuery();
273. 
274. // Queries with skip ΓÇö prevent premature calls
275. const { data } = useGetResourceByIdQuery(id, { skip: !id });
276. 
277. // Mutations ΓÇö call in event handlers
278. const [createResource, { isLoading: isCreating }] = useCreateResourceMutation();
279. 
280. const handleCreate = async () => {
281.   try {
282.     const result = await createResource(payload).unwrap();
283.     // Success ΓÇö navigate or update UI
284.   } catch (err) {
285.     // Error ΓÇö show error state
286.   }
287. };
288. ```
289. 
290. ## Checklist
291. 
292. - [ ] Endpoint constant in `src/libs/http/api-endpoints.ts`
293. - [ ] TypeScript types in `src/types/{feature}.ts`
294. - [ ] `ApiConfig` with `url`, `endpoint`, `builder()`, `mock()`
295. - [ ] Mock has realistic delay (800ΓÇô2000ms)
296. - [ ] Mock returns realistic data matching the TypeScript types
297. - [ ] Hooks exported via `ProtectedApiService`
298. - [ ] Tag type registered in `baseApi.ts` (if new feature)
299. - [ ] `providesTags` on queries, `invalidatesTags` on mutations
300. "
}

